social_posts.post_text: Here are some last sights of my 20’s and first finds of my 30’s. If you would like a deep dive into things I saw and did over the last decade, I documented them well on this phone application. Cheers to the next 30 years of documenting the doing of things before I die.

Ok. So, I tried to delete the original post of this with a worse crop, and sure enough I can most def delete from the original post. BUT I can not replace the photo… so I’m having to make a new post. And here I am explaining why I’m going to post this singular photo (which, mind you, I do not think is that special or awesome, I just liked it and wanted it to go with the set) to absolutely no one. I hope next week is better 🤘🏼

Hey. Anyone know anyone in the arts that has a job with health insurance for a starving diabetic artist who doesn’t want to put together a portfolio and also couldn’t tell you what kind of “art job” he wants? ?

I would very much like to improve my portraiture when it comes to drawing and need help doing so. If you’re interested in me drawing your face, or the face of someone you know, comment or DM. No charge and you get what you get. (If you’re looking for a more refined commission, plz visit my website where I’ll forget to email you back)

Alright, my chip fracture in my left hand has healed and my right hand sprain/contusion has calmed and I was given the OK to start being active again!

That being said: I’m going to be opening up my commissions for 2024 before the end of this year and my photography books are wide open for the next year as well! If you know someone who needs a picture or you yourself are in great want of something made by me, HMU! My hands work again 😎

Now to finally be able to do my chores again.

I did 5 push ups this morning. 😎

I’m really bad at marketing myself because I’d rather be making things. My books for making things are now wide open and I’m ready to create some works of (f)art for whomever is wanting! For inquiry: please email Kevin.gilgan@gmail.com. 

If you’ve reached out to me in the past and still are interested in a commission, please don’t hesitate to reach out again. I’ll give you a big discount as an apology. 

All proceeds go to my insulin addition. #art #diabetes #healthisurnaceissoexpensive #photography #socality
